"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517221","Home Office","false","2016-05-10","<p>UK passports currently recognise only male and female genders. To introduce a third category, such a denoted by an ‘X’ in the passport, would require a change in UK primary legislation.</p><p>The Government is currently considering this issue as part of its response to the report on Transgender Equality by the Women and Equalities Select Committee.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-05-10T16:22:18.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517221/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517221/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517221/answer","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517221/answer/previousversion/59653","Biography information for Karen Bradley","1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-05-03","Passports: Gender","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will issue a response to Early Day Motion 660, Legal recognition for people who do not associate with a particular gender.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","36284"
