e been deregistered as CASCs, affecting some 35 different types of sport.</p><p> </p><p>Since 2010 there has been a steady increase in the numbers of CASCs registered in the scheme. Although the Government does not yet have figures for clubs registered as at 5 April 2016, the breakdown of figures since 2010 is:</p><p> </p><p>5630 – 5 April 2010</p><p>5976 – 5 April 2011</p><p>6165 – 5 April 2012</p><p>6334 – 5 April 2013</p><p>6571 – 5 April 2014</p><p>6715 – 5 April 2015.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","36068 ; 36069 ; 36070 ; 36071 ; 36253","2016-05-11T16:26:24.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516631/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516631/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516631/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-28","Community Amateur Sports Clubs Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many community amateur sports clubs were registered at the end of each financial year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","36099"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516632","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-05-10","<p>The Government has not issued guidance to local authorities on assessing the social and economic value of their local pubs. However, the British Beer and Pub Association estimate that each pub contributes £80,000 each year to its local economy and that the UK pubs industry as a whole supports 900,000 jobs.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-05-10T15:52:07.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516632/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516632/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516632/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-04-28","Public Houses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what guidance his Department has provided to local authorities on assessing the social and economic value of a pub to the local area; and if he will make a statement of the effectiveness of that guidance.","false","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg","36090"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516633","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-05-10","<p>There are over 1,200 pubs that have been listed as assets of community value by communities all over England.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-05-10T15:52:32.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516633/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516633/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516633/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-04-28","Community Assets: Public Houses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many pubs in England have asset of community value status.","false","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg","36091"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516634","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-05-10","<p>The Department has made no specific assessment of the effectiveness of the scheme in protecting community pubs in Sheffield or in England, although my officials are undertaking a review of the implementation of the policy in relation to all assets across the country. They are engaging a broad range of stakeholders - local authorities, community groups, property owners - to listen to their reflections and experiences concerning the policy and any evidence on how the Community Right to Bid is working in practice. The Community Right to Bid is seen by many stakeholders as a powerful way for local people to send a clear signal to their local authorities and to owners of assets that they are keen to have say on the future of buildings which are central to their lives.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-05-10T15:55:15.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516634/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516634/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516634/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-04-28","Community Assets: Public Houses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the assets of community value scheme in protecting community pubs in (a) Sheffield and (b) England.","false","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg","36093"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516635","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-05-10","<p>The Department for Communities and Local Government does not collect this information.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-05-10T15:51:24.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516635/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516635/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516635/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-04-28","Community Assets: Public Houses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what information he holds on the number of community pubs with assets of community value status that have been closed or that no longer operate as a pub.","false","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg","36092"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516636","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-05-10","<p>There is no specific appeals process in place to enable a community to appeal against the rejection of an asset of community value application. If the nominating group feel that the local authority has not followed the due legal process in reaching a decision, the nominating group may bring any such irregularities to the attention of the local authority’s monitoring officer. In addition, if new evidence comes to light to support the case for the asset being listed, the community are able to re-nominate the asset.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-05-10T15:54:04.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516636/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516636/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516636/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-04-28","Community Assets: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what processes are in place to enable a community to appeal against the rejection of an asset of community value application.","false","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg","36087"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516637","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-05-10","<p>I have not received any such representations.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-05-10T15:55:46.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516637/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516637/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516637/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-04-28","Public Houses: Sheffield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what representations he has received from Sheffield City Council on protecting community pubs.","false","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg","36088"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516638","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-05-10","<p>Sheffield City Council has not approached the Department for any discussions on the Assets of Community Value scheme.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-05-10T15:50:42.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516638/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516638/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516638/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-04-28","Community Assets: Sheffield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what discussions his Department has had with Sheffield City Council on the assets of community value scheme.","false","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg","36089"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516639","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-05-04","<p>As part of the rollout of Universal Credit we fund Local Authorities, through Delivery Partnerships, to provide support to claimants which includes support to acquire and improve their digital skills and to make and manage their Universal Credit claim online. There is also budgeting support to help manage their money on a monthly basis and pay bills on time.</p><p> </p><p>How much of this funding is targeted to specific purposes will be determined by the individual partnership and based on local need.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-05-04T16:38:28.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516639/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516639/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516639/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-04-28","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 27 April 2016 to Question 35020, what funding the Government has allocated to local authorities to deliver digital and budgeting support for the roll-out of universal credit.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","36041"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516640","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-05-04","<strong><br />A: </strong>Details on the population of businesses in each of those groups can be found at the following link: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/467443/bpe_2015_statistical_release.pdf" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/467443/bpe_2015_statistical_release.pdf</a>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-05-04T10:09:15.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516640/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516640/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516640/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-04-28","Cybercrime: Small Businesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 26 April 2016 to Question 19259, what estimate he has made of the proportion of (a) micro, (b) small and (c) medium-size businesses that that level of take up represents.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","36042"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516641","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-05-04","<p>It is an offence for an unauthorized person to sell a ticket for a designated football match via the internet under section 166A of the Criminal Justice and Public Order Act 1994. The Government expects companies in the secondary market to comply with the law.</p><p> </p><p>Professor Michael Waterson is chairing an independent Review of consumer protection measures applying to the re-sale of tickets for music, sporting or cultural events in the UK through secondary ticketing facilities. In supporting Professor Waterson in carrying out his Review, my officials have had discussions with their counterparts in the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills and the Home Office about online re-sale of football tickets.</p><p> </p><p>The Department agrees with the Football Association that fans of the home nations participating in the Euro 2016 Football Championships should purchase tickets through authorised channels. Such channels include UEFA’s Euro 2016 ticket resale platform.</p><p> </p><p>The safety and security of the Euro 2016 Football Championships is a matter for the French Government and UEFA. The UK Government co-operates closely with France on matters of policing and security.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett","36016 ; 36018","2016-05-04T12:55:46.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516641/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516641/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516641/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-04-28","Football: Tickets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the potential risks to safety and security posed by the selling of tickets via websites to UK-based customers for the European Football Association Championships in the secondary ticketing market.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","36017"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516642","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-05-04","<p>Current estimates suggest that almost 90% of premises in the Warwick and Leamington constituency are subject to commercial rollout, and a further 5% of premises (2,369) now have coverage as a result of the Government's Superfast Broadband programme.</p><p> </p><p>Based on DCMS modelled estimates and current delivery plans, 96% of premises in the Warwick and Leamington constituency will have access to superfast broadband by December 2017. Early gainshare funding that BT will return in response to the high levels of take-up being achieved, could help extend coverage further.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-05-04T16:00:56.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516642/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516642/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516642/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-04-28","Broadband: Warwick and Leamington","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what progress has been made on the rollout of superfast broadband in (a) Warwick and (b) the Warwick and Leamington constituency.","false","Biography information for Chris White","Warwick and Leamington","Chris White","36025"
